17 (a) Notwithstanding the provisions of Title 10, Subtitle 3 of the State Finance and
18 Procurement Article, [this] THE State may not require reimbursement of debt service from
19 a county for a school that:
20 (1) Was initially constructed on or before February 1, 1971;
21 (2) Is no longer used for [school purposes] A PURPOSE THAT IS ELIGIBLE
22 FOR STATE FUNDING FOR PUBLIC SCHOOL CONSTRUCTION;
23 (3) Has had title transferred to a county government; and
24 (4) Is being used for local governmental purposes other than public
25 education; provided, however, that if a former school building is sold by a county
26 government the State shall be reimbursed for outstanding debt service, and if more than
27 10 percent of usable space within a former school is rented for an amount exceeding the
28 cost of operating and maintaining such space, such rental profit shall be used toward
29 retiring outstanding bonded indebtedness.
30 (b) Subject to subsection (c) of this section, this State shall require reimbursement
31 of outstanding debt service from a county for a school that:

