11 (b) (1) Except as provided in subsection (e) of this section, educational
12 specifications and schematic designs for [major] APPLICABLE construction projects THAT
13 WILL AFFECT THE PLAN CONFIGURATION OF STUDENT–OCCUPIED SPACES IN A
14 SCHOOL BUILDING OR ON ITS GROUNDS are required to:
15 (i) Be reviewed by the Interagency Commission; and
16 (ii) Prior to finalization by a local education agency, have any
17 concerns or recommendations of the Interagency Commission satisfactorily resolved.
18 (2) To provide efficiency within the process, the Department and the
19 Interagency Commission shall consider altering the review and approval process required
20 under paragraph (1) of this subsection, including a rolling deadline for submission of
21 documents, with schematic designs submitted following the completion of the educational
22 specifications review.
23 (c) (1) Change orders for [major] APPLICABLE construction projects and
24 systemic renovation projects may not be:
25 (i) Reviewed by the Department of General Services; and
26 (ii) Approved by the Interagency Commission.
27 (2) A percentage of the State allocation related to change orders may not
28 be withheld.
29 (3) Local education agencies shall maintain contingency funds for each
30 approved project to address unanticipated construction costs above the State allocation.

